        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), or Hodevah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 7:43",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), were the two heads of Levitical families; and their fewness is compensated by their unanimity and vigour. Henadad is not mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", though it is a Levitical name in Nehemiah. Why omitted there, or why inserted here, it is not possible to determine.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
